.TH "omap3xxx_restart" 9 "omap3xxx_restart" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap3xxx_restart \- trigger a software restart of the SoC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" omap3xxx_restart
.BI "(enum reboot_mode mode "  ","
.BI "const char *cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mode" 12
the "reboot mode", see arch/arm/kernel/{setup,process}.c
.IP "cmd" 12
passed from the userspace program rebooting the system (if provided)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Resets the SoC.  For \fIcmd\fP, see the 'reboot' syscall in
kernel/sys.c.  No return value.
